November 7, 1872 the ship Mary Celeste sails away from the port of New York.

2
00:00:16,360 --> 00:00:20,480
The ship would sail to Italy.

3
00:00:20,480 --> 00:00:30,960
On board Mary Celeste was Captain Benjamin S. Briggs.
 His wife Sarah and their 2 year old daughter Sophia

4
00:00:30,960 --> 00:00:34,860
But also 7-8 pieces in the crew.

5
00:00:35,720 --> 00:00:44,200
About a month later, December 5, a British ship named Dei Gratia sails

6
00:00:44,200 --> 00:00:51,260
About 64-74 miles east from the Portuguese archipelago Azores.

7
00:00:51,260 --> 00:01:04,300
The crew of Dei Gratia sees a ship about 10 km away from them.
 The ship behaved strangely.
 It seemed to sail irregularly.

8
00:01:04,300 --> 00:01:07,040
Like no one on board ruled.

9
00:01:07,040 --> 00:01:12,880
They could not see anyone aboard the deck, which was very strange.

10
00:01:13,720 --> 00:01:25,860
The captain of Dei Gratia, David Morehouse suspected that something must be wrong and sent three of his men to go there to investigate.

11
00:01:32,560 --> 00:01:40,640
As the men approached the ship, they saw the name of the ship written on the stern ...

12
00:01:40,640 --> 00:01:44,220
Mary Celeste.

13
00:01:47,380 --> 00:01:56,180
The men climbed aboard the ship.
 Once on board, they discovered that something was not really right.

14
00:01:56,180 --> 00:02:03,960
Many of the sails were broken or in very poor condition.
 Some sails were completely missing.

15
00:02:03,960 --> 00:02:11,620
When you went down into the cargo room it was water -filled up to 1.1 meters.
 A significant amount of water.

16
00:02:11,620 --> 00:02:15,940
But not particularly alarming to a ship of this size.

17
00:02:15,940 --> 00:02:25,140
The men also found a provisional measuring rod that should probably have been used to measure the water depth inside the ship.

18
00:02:25,140 --> 00:02:30,440
It was also discovered that the lifeboat was gone.

19
00:02:30,440 --> 00:02:34,080
The men continue to investigate the ship.

20
00:02:34,080 --> 00:02:45,800
Mary Celeste carried 1701 barrels with industrial alcohol, but all cargo was untouched and mostly intact.

21
00:02:45,800 --> 00:02:50,720
There was food on board that would last for about 6 months.

22
00:02:50,720 --> 00:03:00,960
It was also seen that part of the navigation equipment was gone.
 Among other things, a chronometer, a navigation book and a sextant.

23
00:03:00,960 --> 00:03:14,200
A logbook was found, where it had been noted that Mary Celeste had added to the harbor on the island of Santa Maria, which belongs to the Azores archipelago on November 25.

24
00:03:14,200 --> 00:03:20,680
About 74 km from where the ship was then found by Dei Gratia.

25
00:03:20,680 --> 00:03:27,460
But that note was written about 1.5 weeks ago without any update since then.

26
00:03:27,460 --> 00:03:32,140
There was nothing about any problem or damage to the ship.

27
00:03:32,140 --> 00:03:39,540
There were no signs of violence, injuries or that it had burned on the ship.

28
00:03:39,540 --> 00:03:47,020
Apart from the fact that it was a little wet here and there, the ship was still in a relatively good condition.

29
00:03:47,020 --> 00:03:55,240
The personal possession of the crew and the captain and valuables remained on the ship.

30
00:03:55,240 --> 00:04:00,560
It was like everyone had just ... abandoned the ship.

31
00:04:01,440 --> 00:04:04,440
But why?

32
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:16,320
Mary Celeste quickly became known as the "ghost ship"

33
00:04:16,320 --> 00:04:24,040
And from that name a lot of different theories were born about what may have happened to the crew on board.

34
00:04:24,040 --> 00:04:29,360
Since no one knows what has happened, I will go through 5 different theories

35
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:35,540
And then it is up to everyone to decide what sounds most reasonable.

36
00:04:40,560 --> 00:04:43,160
The theories that I intend to go through are:

37
00:04:43,160 --> 00:04:44,960
MUTINY

38
00:04:44,960 --> 00:04:46,440
Pirates

39
00:04:46,440 --> 00:04:48,140
Water thrombus

