42
00:04:55,920 --> 00:05:01,920
If we look at the first theory.
 Mutiny.
 What does it mean?

43
00:05:01,920 --> 00:05:08,180
Myteri means that, for example, crews on a ship refuse to obey the commander's order.

44
00:05:08,180 --> 00:05:14,140
In some cases, this can lead to rebellion and the crew then become violent.

45
00:05:14,140 --> 00:05:21,660
According to this theory, the crew must be drunk by the alcohol on board, become violent

46
00:05:21,660 --> 00:05:26,300
And then killed Captain Briggs and his family.

47
00:05:26,300 --> 00:05:30,100
But.. There are some problems with this theory.

48
00:05:30,100 --> 00:05:41,920
First, Captain Briggs was known for being a very good captain who had a reputation for always treating his crew well and fairly.

49
00:05:41,920 --> 00:05:50,420
Secondly, the alcohol on board industrial alcohol was.
 Also called denatured alcohol.

50
00:05:50,420 --> 00:05:59,280
It is alcohol that is undrinkable.
 Different chemicals have been added to make it taste bad or even toxic.

51
00:05:59,280 --> 00:06:05,500
This is for the alcohol to be used in other products that are not intended to be consumed.

52
00:06:05,500 --> 00:06:09,960
In today's society this is in hand spirit.

53
00:06:10,500 --> 00:06:21,040
Hence, it is difficult to imagine that the crew would force an alcohol that is not suitable to drink and thus risk their own health.

54
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:34,200
Third, if now the crew murdered the captain and his family, why would all abandon the ship in the middle of the sea in a small lifeboat?

55
00:06:34,200 --> 00:06:37,200
It does not add up.

56
00:06:42,040 --> 00:06:51,900
If we look at the second theory of pirates, it can initially and be a reasonable theory of what may have happened.

57
00:06:51,900 --> 00:06:58,260
The area where Mary Celeste was found was known for having North African pirates.

58
00:06:58,260 --> 00:07:06,480
They may have been so that a bunch of pirates attacked Mary Celeste and killed everyone on board.

59
00:07:06,480 --> 00:07:14,880
But pirates are known to plunder ships.
 So steal away.

60
00:07:14,880 --> 00:07:24,580
But Mary Celeste had all the loads and all valuables from the crew were still left when the ship was found.

61
00:07:24,580 --> 00:07:37,140
This theory thus also becomes unlikely because it is difficult to imagine that pirates would murder an entire crew in "unnecessary" without getting anything for it.

62
00:07:37,140 --> 00:07:45,500
Could it have been that the crew aboard Dei Gratia has anything to do with it?

63
00:07:45,500 --> 00:07:55,080
Maybe it was those who attacked Mary Celeste, killed everyone on board and pretended to find the ship empty and on operation

64
