Can the sea itself be behind the disappearance of the crew?

67
00:08:14,780 --> 00:08:20,300
I mean, it is no wonder that there are natural disasters out on the sea.

68
00:08:20,300 --> 00:08:23,300
A theory points to this.

69
00:08:23,300 --> 00:08:33,060
That it was a water thrombus, also called sea straw that may have created the flood down in the cargo room at Mary Celeste.

70
00:08:33,060 --> 00:08:40,140
Then the crew may have used the provisional measuring rod to measure the water mass and probably believed it would

71
00:08:40,140 --> 00:08:48,600
continue to rise and that the ship would sink.
 Hence, all the ship fled via the lifeboat.

72
00:08:48,600 --> 00:08:55,040
In that case, it would explain why it was so wet everywhere inside the ship.

73
